copyBlock.cwc:
How do I make a balloon arch at home?

Balloon arches look complicated but can be put together quite easily, especially if you purchase a balloon arch kit so that you have everything you need. You use balloon arch tape which is like sticky tape but with holes to put your balloon knots through to mark out where you want the arch to go. Then, you add the blown-up balloons to the tape, in the creative way you choose.

What’s the best way to stop my helium balloon from blowing away?

Helium balloons will float away if you don’t tie them down, but this is relatively easy to do. Use balloon weights or tie them to centerpieces, chairs, or other decorations.

Do I need a pump to make balloon animals?

It’s not easy to blow up the balloons designed for balloon animals by hand, so a hand pump is recommended. If you are frequently making balloon animals, in a large volume, a floor pump may also be a good investment.
